# File Operation Best Practices

- Read a file before editing it.
- Use absolute paths for reads and edits when a tool requires them.
- Make edit search strings unique with enough surrounding context.
- For small changes, read the file and then apply a targeted edit.
- For new files, create the file explicitly with the complete intended content.
- Do not modify files that do not exist unless creating them is the goal.
- When replacing a repeated value, make sure a replace-all operation is intentional.
- Avoid broad "fix everything" edits without first understanding the relevant logic.
